Package: decompTumor2Sig
Type: Package
Title: Decomposition of individual tumors into mutational signatures
    by signature refitting
Depends: R(>= 4.6), ggplot2
Imports: methods, Matrix, quadprog(>= 1.5-5), GenomicRanges, stats, rlang,
    GenomicFeatures, Biostrings, BiocGenerics, S4Vectors, plyr, utils, graphics,
    BSgenome.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg38, TxDb.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg38.knownGene,
    VariantAnnotation, SummarizedExperiment, ggseqlogo, gridExtra, data.table,
    GenomeInfoDb, readxl
Suggests: knitr, rmarkdown, cosmicsig, BiocStyle
Version: 2.99.0
Date: 2026-07-07
Encoding: UTF-8
Authors@R: c(
    person("Rosario M.", "Piro", email = "rmpiro@gmail.com",
            role = c("aut", "cre"), comment=c(ORCID="0000-0002-3066-7397")),
    person("Sandra", "Krueger", role = c("ctb"))
    )
Description: Uses quadratic programming for signature refitting, i.e., to
    decompose the mutation catalog from an individual tumor sample into a set of
    given mutational signatures (either Alexandrov-model signatures or
    Shiraishi-model signatures), computing weights that reflect the
    contributions of the signatures to the mutation load of the tumor.
